A true and certaine relation of a strange-birth which was borne at Stone-house in the parish of Plimmouth, the 20. of October. 1635. Together with the notes of a sermon, preached Octob. 23. 1635. in the church of Plimmouth, at the interring of the sayd birth. By Th. B. B.D. Pr. Pl. Bedford, Thomas, d. 1653.
14, 13-22 p. : ill.
Printed by Anne Griffin, for William Russell in Plim mouth, London : 1635.
Th. B. = Thomas Bedford. Identified as STC 1791a on UMI microfilm. A variant of the edition printed for A. Bowler (STC 1791). Reproduction of the original in the Folger Shakespeare Library.
